<h2>What is FreeCash?</h2>
<p>FreeCash is a rewards platform (sometimes called a GPT or "get-paid-to" site) that pays you for completing tasks. These tasks include playing mobile games to a certain level, signing up for free trials, taking surveys, watching videos, and testing apps.</p>
<p>Unlike some shadier sites in this space, FreeCash is legit. They've paid out over $50 million to users since launching, have a Trustpilot score above 4.5, and actually process withdrawals quickly — usually within 24 hours.</p>

<h2>How Does It Work?</h2>
<p>The concept is simple: advertisers pay FreeCash to get users to try their products (apps, games, services). FreeCash passes a portion of that payment to you as a reward. You're essentially getting paid to be an early adopter.</p>
<p>Here's the typical flow:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Create a free account on FreeCash</li>
  <li>Browse the "offer wall" — a list of available tasks</li>
  <li>Pick an offer (e.g., "Play Raid: Shadow Legends to level 15 — earn $12")</li>
  <li>Complete the task and submit proof</li>
  <li>Get credited and cash out</li>
</ol>

<h2>What Can You Earn?</h2>
<p>Earnings vary a lot depending on what offers are available in your region and how much time you put in. Here's a realistic breakdown:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Casual (1-2 hours/week):</strong> $20-50/month</li>
  <li><strong>Regular (5-10 hours/week):</strong> $100-300/month</li>
  <li><strong>Power user (15+ hours/week):</strong> $400-800/month</li>
</ul>
<p>The highest-paying offers are typically mobile game offers (play to a certain level) and financial product signups (open a free banking app, etc.). Survey-only earnings will be lower — around $3-8/hour.</p>

<h2>Gaming Offers Specifically</h2>
<p>This is where FreeCash shines for gamers. The gaming offers pay well and are actually fun. You'll see tasks like:</p>
